  "texts": [
    "Among Authors in 26 included the difficulties encountered in ambient sound classification (ESC), sometimes called Sound Event Recognition (SER), as a result of variables such as different frameworks, overlapping sound events, numerous sound sources, and non-uniform distances between microphones and acoustic sources.",
    "The fast integration of ESC tasks into many everyday contexts encourages the search for efficient approaches.",
    "To improve the performance of ESC tasks, the study uses deep convolutional neural networks (DCNN) that have been trained using regularisation and data improvement using fundamental audio properties.",
    "The performance of two deep convolutional neural network (DCNN) models is compared: Model-2 without max-pooling and Model-1 with max-pooling.",
    "We take a look at three benchmark datasets-ESC-10, ESC-50, and Urban sound (US8K)-and three methods for extracting audio features: Mel spectrogram (Mel), Mel frequency cepstral coefficient (MFCC), and Log-Mel."
  ],
